#: ../../../cmds/trap.rst:4
msgid "trap - perform an action when the shell receives a signal"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/trap.rst:7
msgid "Synopsis"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/trap.rst:9
msgid "trap [OPTIONS] [[ARG] REASON ... ]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/trap.rst:14
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/trap.rst:16
msgid ""
"``trap`` is a wrapper around the fish event delivery framework. It exists "
"for backwards compatibility with POSIX shells. For other uses, it is "
"recommended to define an :ref:`event handler <event>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/trap.rst:18
msgid "The following parameters are available:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/trap.rst:20
msgid "*ARG*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/trap.rst:21
msgid "Command to be executed on signal delivery."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/trap.rst:23
msgid "*REASON*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/trap.rst:24
msgid ""
"Name of the event to trap. For example, a signal like ``INT`` or ``SIGINT``, "
"or the special symbol ``EXIT``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/trap.rst:26
msgid "**-l** or **--list-signals**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/trap.rst:27
msgid "Prints a list of signal names."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/trap.rst:29
msgid "**-p** or **--print**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/trap.rst:30
msgid "Prints all defined signal handlers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/trap.rst:32
msgid "**-h** or **--help**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/trap.rst:33
msgid "Displays help about using this command."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/trap.rst:35
msgid ""
"If *ARG* and *REASON* are both specified, *ARG* is the command to be "
"executed when the event specified by *REASON* occurs (e.g., the signal is "
"delivered)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/trap.rst:37
msgid ""
"If *ARG* is absent (and there is a single *REASON*) or ``-``, each specified "
"signal is reset to its original disposition (the value it had upon entrance "
"to the shell).  If *ARG* is the null string the signal specified by each "
"*REASON* is ignored by the shell and by the commands it invokes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/trap.rst:39
msgid ""
"If *ARG* is not present and **-p** has been supplied, then the trap commands "
"associated with each *REASON* are displayed. If no arguments are supplied or "
"if only **-p** is given, ``trap`` prints the list of commands associated "
"with each signal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/trap.rst:41
msgid ""
"Signal names are case insensitive and the ``SIG`` prefix is optional. "
"Trapping a signal will prevent fish from exiting in response to that signal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/trap.rst:43
msgid ""
"The exit status is 1 if any *REASON* is invalid; otherwise trap returns 0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/trap.rst:46
msgid "Example"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/trap.rst:52
msgid ""
"trap \"status --print-stack-trace\" SIGUSR1\n"
"# Prints a stack trace each time the SIGUSR1 signal is sent to the shell."
msgstr ""
